org.certificateservices.custom.c2x.ieee1609dot2.datastructs.basic

Class EccP256CurvePoint

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.certificateservices.custom.c2x.asn1.coer.COERChoice
      • org.certificateservices.custom.c2x.ieee1609dot2.datastructs.basic.EccCurvePoint
        • org.certificateservices.custom.c2x.ieee1609dot2.datastructs.basic.EccP256CurvePoint
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, COEREncodable, Encodable

    public class EccP256CurvePoint
extends EccCurvePoint
    This structure specifies a point on an elliptic curve in Weierstrass form defined over a 256-bit prime number. This encompasses both NIST p256 as defined in FIPS 186-4 and Brainpool p256r1 as defined in RFC 5639. The fields in this structure are OCTET STRINGS produced with the elliptic curve point encoding and decoding methods defined in IEEE Std 1363-2000 clause 5.5.6. The x-coordinate is encoded as an unsigned integer of length 32 octets in network byte order for all values of the CHOICE; the encoding of the y-coordinate y depends on whether the point is x-only, compressed, or uncompressed. If the point is x-only, y is omitted. If the point is compressed, the value of type depends on the least significant bit of y: if the least significant bit of y is 0, type takes the value compressed-y-0, and if the least significant bit of y is 1, type takes the value compressed-y-1. If the point is uncompressed, y is encoded explicitly as an unsigned integer of length 32 octets in network byte order.
